6:
Hey, anyone home? We're here on a
quest from the Guild. Looking for
someone named Jester!
14:
Much thanks for accepting the job.
Allow me to show you home sweet
ranch.
18:
Before we begin... The contract offered
danger money. What risks will we be
facing?
22:
Oh, don't you worry about that. Just
some insurance policy to make sure
none of y'all would have a case
against me in court! Haha.
28:
And that concludes our tour of the
ranch. Now, I was going to start you
two off tending the cattle, but do you
have any questions?
33:
Nope. We got it. We're going to make
these cows feel like royalty.
38:
Heh. Sounds like an eager little mouse
came scurrying into my trap.
41:
Trap?
Then that explosion was your doing.
46:
Sure was! I design and rig my own
snares. Got to give even unwelcome
guests a hearty welcome.
56:
Unless you can skin a monster with
your eyes, I suggest you stop staring
and pick up a knife. These pelts are
mighty useful.
60:
So the snares not only protect the
ranch, they are a way to harvest
materials. A clever design.
64:
Of course it is! I am a rancher by day
and a world-class trapper,
also by day.
70:
All right! Let's get down to business
then. Lemme just drop my bag over
here...
74:
Phew... Hey, Jester, what do you think?
Did I get everything?
79:
Yeah, looks good to me. You're pretty
handy with a knife, eh? I wouldn't mind
contracting you just to help me carve
up animals.
82:
Oh. Well, I mean,
this is just like meal prep...
88:
Heh-heh. Oh, you poor monster with
no brain. It ain't possible to slip past
MY nets.
101:
Lured them with food, did you?
You don't only have deft fingers,
you got a quick brain too.
104:
I know! Why don't I take you in as
permanent hands? Teach you all the
finer points of trap-making!
109:
It seems we've gained an
eccentric ally...
